开启更有意思的武汉！请点击上方优良better→点击右上角“...” → “设为星标 ”在这个春节，“隔离”替代“团聚”成了主题。
Open a more interesting Wuhan! Click on the top right corner of "..." to set up the star sign In this Spring Festival, the replacement of "reunion" by "isolation" has become the theme.
1月23日，上午10时，武汉开始“封城”。
On January 23, at 10 a.m., Wuhan began to "seal the city."
交通的阻断，出行的限制，让远在外地的武汉伢回不来，还在武汉的外地人走不了。
Traffic disruption, restrictions on travel, so far away in Wuhan so unable to return, still in Wuhan outsiders can not walk.
医护人员在前线，我们只能在电视、手机屏幕前，感慨他们的不易。
Medical staff are on the front line, we can only in front of the TV, mobile phone screen, sigh that they are not easy.
人与人、人与城、城与城开始隔离后，武汉陷入从未有过的空旷和安静。
When people began to isolate themselves from each other, from the city and from the city, Wuhan fell into the emptiness and silence that had never existed before.
“楼间喊话”“同唱国歌”“共点星光”……隔离中，我们不断为打破“隔离”而努力。
"House shouting", "with singing the national anthem" and "Starlight"... In isolation, we continue to work to break "isolation."
当春节假期被延长，这场“隔离”还将延续。
When the Spring Festival is extended, this "isolation" will continue.
难道，我们就只能坐以待毙，让自己和这座城市长久“隔离”？我开始思考：有什么方法能让在家中的我们和武汉连接在一起？昨晚，我在一场叫做“隔离”的线上艺术计划中，找到了问题的答案。
Can we just sit back and let ourselves be isolated from the city for so long? I began to wonder what could be done to connect us at home to Wuhan? Last night, I found the answer to a question in an online art project called "Segregation."
点击跳转，查看艺术计划详情在这场由合美术馆发起的线上艺术计划里，我看到的都是，人和城市从未被隔离的证据。
Click Jump, See Art Project Details In this online art program sponsored by the Art Gallery, all I see is evidence that people and cities are never segregated.
（以下作品由发起方搜集，仅作样例示范）最好的相机，是人的眼睛。
(The following work was collected by the sponsor as a sample only) The best camera is the human eye.
在这段特殊时期里，我们看到的每一幕都将成为一个历史时刻。
In this particular period, every scene we see will be a moment in history.
灾难把过往的平常，变得无常。
Catastrophes change the ordinary course of events.
每一个快门按下时的武汉，都是独一无二。
Each shutter press when Wuhan, are unique.
来源：艺术家 柯明1月23日，“封城”第一天，up主林晨同学从楚河汉街“起飞”，在超市“降落”，将“空城”武汉传遍全国。
The first day of the "seal" day, students from the Chu River Han Street, "landed" in the supermarket, "empty city" Wuhan spread all over the country.
1月24日，“封城”第二天，摄影师杨柯带着口罩在静得出奇的武汉三镇穿行，记录。
Photographer Yang Ke wore a mask as he made his way through the strangely quiet town of Wuhan on January 24, the day after the city was closed.
1月29日，他们的视频素材，出现在人民日报发布的《武汉加油》MV中，引得全国人民都来给武汉鼓励。
On January 29, their video material, appearing in the People's Daily's "Come on Wuhan" MV, attracted the people of the whole country to give Wuhan encouragement.
个人的记录、集体的创作，宏大的、微小的，都是此时的武汉经历的。
The individual record, the collective creation, the grandeur, the tiny, are all at this time Wuhan experienced.
Play《摄影师镜头下的今日武汉》 麦克视频&摄影师 杨柯Play来源：哔哩哔哩 UP主：林晨同学Play来源：腾讯视频 人民日报“生傲骨，不认输，抗病毒，定胜出！踏疆土，肩重负，武汉有我们守护！”为全国一线医务工作者和所有武汉人民写得这首歌，制作者们全程隔离“云创作”，在 26小时完成。
